# Health Coach agent configuration (TEMPLATE)
# Copy to ~/.claudeclaw-os/agents/health/agent.yaml and fill in your values.
#
# Add your bot token to ~/.env:
#   HEALTH_BOT_TOKEN=1234567890:AAFxxxxxxx
# Start with:
#   npm start -- --agent health

name: Health Coach
description: A personal health coach grounded in your bloods, genetics, body composition, and wearable. Logs everything to Supabase and runs a daily morning check-in.

# The env var in ~/.env holding this bot's Telegram token (create via @BotFather).
telegram_bot_token_env: HEALTH_BOT_TOKEN

# A health coach benefits from strong reasoning. For Claude:
provider:
  type: claude
  model: claude-sonnet-4-6
# Or use OpenCode's configured default:
# provider:
#   type: opencode

# Render structured/tabular replies as rich Telegram HTML (aligned tables, bold).
rich_messages: true

# This coach reaches Supabase through scripts/db.py + scripts/mem.py (service-role
# REST), so no MCP servers are needed.
mcp_servers: []

# Per-agent slash commands. Each registers in this bot's Telegram "/" menu and,
# because it carries a prompt, expands into a canonical instruction when invoked.
commands:
  - command: healthdb
    description: Open the Health OS trends dashboard
    # (Handled natively if you wire a dashboard; otherwise remove.)

  - command: newday
    description: Open today, close out yesterday, reset targets
    prompt: >-
      It is a new day. Run scripts/state.py. If yesterday's daily_checkins row has
      no coach_summary, close it out first (summarize yesterday's totals and
      adherence, and include the recovery story: last night's recovery and the
      one-line cause tying it to yesterday). Then upsert today's daily_checkins
      row and reply with a short Day N header that OPENS with last night's recovery
      line, today's plan gated on that recovery, and the running targets reset for
      today. Phone-first, no em dashes.

  - command: today
    description: Today's totals plus last night's recovery
    prompt: >-
      Run scripts/state.py --today and relay the current picture, phone-first.
      OPEN with last night's recovery line (recovery %, sleep, HRV), then the
      running totals (weight, calories, protein, caffeine, BP). If recovery is red
      or sleep was short, add one line on what that means for the rest of today.

  - command: sofar
    description: Today so far, a rich table of calories, protein, and more
    prompt: >-
      Run scripts/state.py --sofar and reply with its stdout exactly as your whole
      message, not wrapped in a code fence. It is a markdown table the gateway
      renders into a rich Telegram table.

  - command: checkin
    description: Run the morning check-in now
    prompt: >-
      Run the full morning check-in now (same flow as the scheduled job). Read
      state.py first. OPEN with last night's recovery line, then close the loop:
      walk through yesterday honestly against the owner's genetics and tie those
      food/caffeine/training choices to why recovery landed where it did. Note
      supplement adherence only if there's an exception. Check the trend including
      the multi-day sleep/recovery pattern and whether BP has been logged. Give
      today's plan GATED on this morning's recovery. Then ask only what the
      wearable can't tell you: weight, any BP reading, and how they feel. Do NOT
      ask how they slept. Phone-first, no em dashes, end with one focus.

  - command: supplements
    description: Your weekly supplement schedule, daytime and nighttime
    prompt: >-
      Run scripts/supplements.py and reply with its stdout exactly, not wrapped in
      a code fence. It is markdown tables the gateway renders for Telegram.

  - command: advice
    description: Ask the influencer KB, get cited tips reconciled with your data
    prompt: >-
      The owner wants advice from the influencer knowledge base (the influencer_tips
      RAG). Run scripts/advice.py "<their question>" --k 6 and present 2 to 4 of the
      most on-point cited tips, then reconcile them against the owner's own data
      (labs, genetics, goals), which always wins. Do NOT log this as a data point.
